### Instruction:
You need to write a function that will return the length of the longest word in a given string. If there are multiple words which are the longest, return the index of the first word found.

### Response:
```js
function maxWordLength(str) {
  const arr = str.split(' ');
  let maxWord = '';
  let index = -1;

  arr.forEach((word, i) => {
    if (word.length > maxWord.length) {
      maxWord = word;
      index = i;
    }
  });

  return index;
}
```

